. auf einer Erholungs- und Badereise nach Thüringen und dem Rheinland, auf der er noch einmal Goethe trifft, und als Rektor der Berliner Universität (1815/16).  aFriedrich Schleiermacher (1768–1834) was a prodigious letter-writer. Volume 13 of the fifth section of this critical edition of Schleiermacher’s complete works contains his correspondence from July 1813 to December 1816. At the moment of the victory over Napoleon that he himself had longed for, he became increasingly despondent about political developments in Prussia and the time that the events of the day had cost him for his own projects.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 4aKirchengeschichte. 4aKirchenpolitik. 4aNapoleon. 4aRestauration. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh  aHistory of Prussia.  aNapoleon.  achurch history.  achurch politics.  ahistory of philosophy.1 aGerber, Simon, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchmidt, Sarah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020z9783110704570oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311061879240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311066540640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110665406423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110665406/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020